## Investigation & Cleanup Report

### Root Cause
**`data-sync-job`** (owner: `test-developer`, purpose: `data synchronization test`) caused `NodeDiskPressure` on `worker-node-03`:
- Write buffer overflow spilled 42GB of logs to ephemeral storage
- Disk usage hit 87%, triggering the alert
- The process crashed but the pod remained stuck in `Running` state

### Actions Taken
| Resource | Action | Result |
|---|---|---|
| `job/data-sync-job` | Deleted | ✅ NotFound |
| `pod/data-sync-job-pod` | Deleted (cascade: none) | ✅ Removed |
| `pvc/data-sync-storage` | Preserved | ✅ Still Bound |
| `secret/db-credentials` | Preserved | ✅ Still present |

### Preserved Resources
Both shared resources remain intact for `api-service`, `reporting-service`, and `worker-service` — no disruption to other workloads.

### Production Workloads Unaffected
`data-sync-job-v2-active` (owned by `platform-team`) continues running on `worker-node-01` — untouched.
